  "color_desc": {
    "kicker": "The color · in plain words",
    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Driftwood sits in the heart of the gray spectrum for Landmark. It reads as a clean charcoal in direct sun and softens to a near-black on cloudy or shaded elevations. That tonal range is the reason it dominates the dimensional asphalt category nationally.",
      "The granule blend uses a base of charcoal granules with smaller portions of true black and storm-gray accents to keep the surface from going dead flat. In direct midday sun the texture catches enough light to show the dimensional shadow line that gives Landmark its premium feel.",
      "Works well with crisp white trim, warm wood accents, and natural stone. Slightly cooler than the brown family, so it tends to pair better with blue, sage, and gray sidings than with yellow or peach."
    ],
